<item>
            <title>[LU-17167] &apos;nrs_tbf_client&apos; is badly named</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17167</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;nrs_tbf_client&lt;/tt&gt; structure is badly named.  This might have represented the state of a single client for the original TBF  implementation that was a node-based rate, but it no longer makes sense for the current TBF implementation that may have rate limits for UID/GID/JobID, etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better to rename this as &lt;tt&gt;nrs_tbf_class&lt;/tt&gt; or similar, and use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ntc&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; as the variable name instead of &quot;&lt;tt&gt;cli&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are also a number of functions related to this, like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;nrs_tbf_cli_init()&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; that also need to be renamed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
